1
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:10,000
[Episode 13: 25 is Fine]

2
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:12,680
Sorry, we...

3
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:14,074
It's me.

4
00:01:15,599 --> 00:01:17,000
I come to cook.

5
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,246
Wait.

6
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:27,810
Come in, please.

7
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,840
I wrote the rest smoothly.

8
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,085
Thank you.

9
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,458
You're welcome.

10
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:49,575
Soak to de-fishy, right?

11
00:01:52,427 --> 00:01:53,440
Blanch for 2 min.

12
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:55,580
Any longer and the meat will get tough.

13
00:01:56,610 --> 00:01:57,880
You're well prepared.

14
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:59,160
Sure.

15
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,720
And it needs to be dry to prevent

16
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,697
splattering when pan-fried.

17
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,359
Shouldn't it be stir-fried over high heat?

18
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,879
Stir-fry slowly over medium to low heat

19
00:02:08,879 --> 00:02:10,680
to remove the moisture and oil of cicadas.

20
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:13,319
This makes the shells crispy but not hard.

21
00:02:13,319 --> 00:02:14,668
Like this.

22
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,040
But you make sense.

23
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,960
Quick-frying over high heat
makes a dish more fragrant.

24
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:25,680
It's proper heat for seasoning.

25
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:27,036
Right?

26
00:02:43,476 --> 00:02:44,946
It smells good.

27
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:50,251
Have a bite.

28
00:02:51,236 --> 00:02:52,630
Try it.

29
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:56,200
Try it.

30
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,713
Why are you avoiding me?

31
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,600
I'm not.

32
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,090
It's just...

33
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,813
sometimes too close.

34
00:03:08,072 --> 00:03:11,125
It's your set distance,

35
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,497
right?

36
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,570
30 cm.

37
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,840
25.

38
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:28,040
I mean,

39
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:29,629
25 is fine.

40
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:51,000
[Spring]

41
00:03:51,796 --> 00:03:56,800
[Wild Fish]

42
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:02,640
Today is the grand opening of Hongxia Diner.

43
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,800
We look forward to serving you!

44
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,800
Thank you for coming.

45
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:09,001
Congrats.

46
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:14,502
One, two, three.

47
00:04:15,190 --> 00:04:16,401
Yeah.

48
00:04:17,381 --> 00:04:18,400
[Hongxia Diner]

49
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,854
- Good.
- Come. Please come to the hall.

50
00:04:21,854 --> 00:04:23,255
Come in.

51
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:26,070
This is my room.

52
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:27,840
Don't squeeze.

53
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:30,071
The kitchen is on the right.

54
00:04:30,071 --> 00:04:31,520
It's renovated.

55
00:04:31,520 --> 00:04:34,145
Over there, it's the dining room.

56
00:04:34,145 --> 00:04:35,100
[Open]

57
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,661
[Closed]

58
00:04:45,505 --> 00:04:46,920
Are you nuts?

59
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:48,680
You don't want it, but I do.

60
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,905
It's the last day.

61
00:04:49,905 --> 00:04:51,400
You won't be able to eat it tomorrow.

62
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,400
Who said I don't want it?

63
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:56,600
It's for Xi Zhou's guests. You can't eat it.

64
00:04:57,493 --> 00:05:00,560
You only eat organic food, don't you?

65
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,886
So?

66
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:06,352
Aren't you replacing the cracked one?

67
00:05:07,252 --> 00:05:08,440
Actually your paintings

68
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,825
aren't selling well, are they?

69
00:05:10,825 --> 00:05:12,360
Who says?

70
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,326
They're in short supply!

71
00:05:20,990 --> 00:05:22,350
What?

72
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,240
You haven't been on set for so long.

73
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,920
Are you not getting any roles?

74
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,040
I'm picky about scripts, okay?

75
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:32,310
"I'm picky about scripts, okay?"

76
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,240
<i>Annoying Zhu Qiao Fei.</i>

77
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:54,586
<i>Now I need to buy a new screen.</i>

78
00:05:59,439 --> 00:06:01,888
<i>I have to sell some clothes.</i>

79
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:09,502
<i>This is my favorite dress!</i>

80
00:06:22,545 --> 00:06:24,472
[Certificate of Completion]
[Outstanding Student]

81
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:41,296
I look forward to working with you.

82
00:06:49,279 --> 00:06:50,840
<i>Actually your paintings</i>

83
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,495
<i>aren't selling well, are they?</i>

84
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:00,039
Bento, Bento,

85
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,626
you're fed.

86
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:07,102
But how long will I wait?

87
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,920
<i>You haven't been on set for so long.</i>

88
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:12,200
<i>Are you not getting any roles?</i>

89
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,480
Change the price to 200 yuan, and I'll take it.

90
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,040
450 yuan at least.

91
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,480
Fill all the blanks,

92
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,320
and I'll pay 300 yuan.

93
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,879
Leave it blank!

94
00:07:28,879 --> 00:07:30,480
It'll lose its charm if filled.

95
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,120
I don't appreciate your style.

96
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,995
200 yuan. I'm a student. And I'm serious.

97
00:07:36,410 --> 00:07:38,362
You know nothing about art!

98
00:07:44,642 --> 00:07:47,131
300 yuan, and I'll fill it for you.

99
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,693
300 yuan.

100
00:08:14,839 --> 00:08:16,402
One yuan

101
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:33,737
can buy a popsicle at least.

102
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,906
Hello?

103
00:08:41,779 --> 00:08:43,828
Eunuch? I can.

104
00:08:43,828 --> 00:08:45,210
I can, I can.

105
00:08:45,919 --> 00:08:47,795
Qing palace drama...

106
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:50,521
Can I wear a wig?

107
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,600
I see.

108
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,800
I can be shaven.

109
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:57,142
Is shaving... free?

110
00:08:58,039 --> 00:08:59,223
Okay.

111
00:09:02,698 --> 00:09:04,355
[Nanwan Temple Fair]
Come and take a look!

112
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,360
Come, come!

113
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:09,159
- Let me see.
- Yes.

114
00:09:09,159 --> 00:09:10,320
A prize!

115
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,720
- Excuse me.
- Not bad.

116
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:14,120
You know what, you're sure to win.

117
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,678
Sure.

118
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,445
What's the distance?

119
00:09:20,181 --> 00:09:22,399
[Nanwan Temple Fair]

120
00:09:22,399 --> 00:09:24,800
Don't worry. I'll be on set soon.

121
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:26,279
W-What?

122
00:09:26,279 --> 00:09:27,560
You have a bald guest actor

123
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:29,160
and could save on shaving?

124
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:31,240
Well, then. Look forward to our next...

125
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,532
cooperation.

126
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,695
Can I get by?

127
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,307
Compared to Florida,

128
00:09:48,307 --> 00:09:50,687
the sunset here is more beautiful.

129
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,639
What's on your mind?

130
00:09:54,639 --> 00:09:56,725
You're absent-minded.

131
00:10:02,879 --> 00:10:04,288
May I ask?

132
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,799
You heard him say "Can I get by?"

133
00:10:08,799 --> 00:10:10,678
when he was near you, right?

134
00:10:11,352 --> 00:10:13,360
Even if he didn't ask, others would move aside.

135
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,160
Or he could say "Excuse me".

136
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,720
But he asked "Can I?"

137
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,680
He already knew the answer.

138
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:21,368
He wanted to look considerate.

139
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,879
Don't you think it's sly?

140
00:10:23,879 --> 00:10:25,520
You mean I'm sly?

141
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:29,288
I mean you can say directly. It's okay.

142
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,800
Earlier,

143
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,800
Li Nan Xi asked you why you weren't

144
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,399
working in Florence.

145
00:10:37,399 --> 00:10:39,325
You said you came back for a visit.

146
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,311
Wasn't it Florida?

147
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,799
<i>You have a rich dad, don't you?</i>

148
00:10:46,799 --> 00:10:48,159
<i>Why the secondhand?</i>

149
00:10:48,159 --> 00:10:50,240
<i>Every penny saved counts.</i>

150
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:52,519
<i>Aren't you working in Florence?</i>

151
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:54,159
<i>I came back for a break.</i>

152
00:10:54,159 --> 00:10:55,680
<i>A man working all day</i>

153
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,630
<i>is like a beast of burden.</i>

154
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:00,960
They're similar.

155
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,608
So I didn't notice.

156
00:11:10,981 --> 00:11:12,694
Why are you silent?

157
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:21,880
It's like someone holding a kettle

158
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:23,890
and shouting "Boiling water" in the crowd.

159
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:26,896
If you don't want to move aside,

160
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,367
you need to prove

161
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:31,334
there's no boiling water in it.

162
00:11:34,621 --> 00:11:38,240
However, dwelling on trivialities‌

163
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,385
makes one unreasonable.

164
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,265
I'll have to stop here.

165
00:11:45,179 --> 00:11:47,640
If my kettle has no boiling water,

166
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:49,480
will you be angry?

167
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,272
Yes,

168
00:11:51,272 --> 00:11:53,001
because it's insincere.

169
00:11:56,814 --> 00:11:59,906
You're not that kind of person, are you?

170
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,167
Sure.

171
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:04,045
I always say "Excuse me".

172
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,309
Mom. Look.

173
00:12:21,018 --> 00:12:22,981
[Nanwan Temple Fair]

174
00:13:20,879 --> 00:13:22,680
You want me to be in a drama?

175
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:24,320
At least pay that sum.

176
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:27,580
I can customize the KT panels for the stage.

177
00:13:27,580 --> 00:13:29,280
But acting?

178
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,720
No way.

179
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,101
What a pity.

180
00:13:32,101 --> 00:13:34,679
With a professional art director,

181
00:13:34,679 --> 00:13:36,640
and Xiang Nan Feng as the script supervisor,

182
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:40,613
it aims to create a multi-dimensional,
complicated and challenging role.

183
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,627
I'm in!

184
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:46,680
Didn't you want to be the sign holder?

185
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:49,520
A sign holder is the sole lead.

186
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:51,120
Acting on stage?

187
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:53,439
I don't want to be a supporting role.

188
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,799
What a pity.

189
00:13:55,799 --> 00:13:57,570
I want you to be the lead,

190
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:59,800
thus invite a handsome man
to play the supporting role,

191
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,360
and a celebrated scriptwriter
as the script supervisor.

192
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,658
I'm in!

193
00:14:06,360 --> 00:14:08,440
You're getting something for nothing.

194
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:10,120
I'll write the script myself.

195
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,600
You just need to review and make suggestions.

196
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:14,799
I'll revise it. You needn't write.

197
00:14:14,799 --> 00:14:16,320
That's not the point.

198
00:14:16,320 --> 00:14:18,800
You're not experienced in scriptwriting.

199
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:22,080
I plan to adapt a well-known play.

200
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,000
As compensation, I can plow, irrigate

201
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,720
and disinfest your plot.

202
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,639
Whatever you offer, I'm not in.

203
00:14:27,639 --> 00:14:28,851
Or...

204
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:33,596
I can inspire you.

205
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:37,023
What do you take me for?

206
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:45,187
I'm sending the script to everyone.

207
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:50,480
I'll play Zhu Ying Tai?

208
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:51,960
You'll play the female role,

209
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:54,799
very multi-dimension, complicated
and challenging!

210
00:14:54,799 --> 00:14:57,440
I'll play Liang Shan Bo?

211
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,360
You're the lead, with a handsome man

212
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,440
as the supporting role.

213
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:03,978
So Ma Wen Cai is...

214
00:15:03,978 --> 00:15:05,360
Is...

215
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,677
Me!
